soc.game

Class SOCTradeOffer

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.game.SOCTradeOffer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class SOCTradeOffer
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    This class represents a trade offer in Settlers of Catan and/or is part of a network message about trades.
    See Also:

      • SOCTradeOffer

        public SOCTradeOffer(java.lang.String game,
                     int from,
                     boolean[] to,
                     SOCResourceSet give,
                     SOCResourceSet get)
        The constructor for a SOCTradeOffer
        Parameters:
        game - the name of the game in which this offer was made
        from - the number of the player making the offer
        to - a boolean array with the set of player numbers this offer is made to; see getTo() for details. Not null.
        give - the set of resources being given (offered) by the from player; not null
        get - the set of resources being asked for; not null

      • getTo

        public boolean[] getTo()
        Get the set of player numbers this offer is made to: An array with SOCGame.maxPlayers elements, where to[pn] is true for each player number to whom the offer was made. For reply status, see getWaitingReply() or isWaitingReplyFrom(int).
        Returns:
        the array showing to which player numbers this offer was made

      • getWaitingReply

        public boolean[] getWaitingReply()
        Get the set of player numbers this offer is made to, who haven't replied yet (reject or accept). A subset of getTo().

        For individual players, see isWaitingReplyFrom(int).

        Returns:
        the boolean array representing player numbers to whom this offer was made: An array with SOCGame.maxPlayers elements, set true for the SOCPlayer.getPlayerNumber() of each player to whom the offer was made but no reject/accept reply has been received.
        Since:
        2.0.00

      • isWaitingReplyFrom

        public boolean isWaitingReplyFrom(int pn)
        Is offer still waiting for a reply from this player?

        For all players, see getWaitingReply().

        Threads: Not synchronized; caller must synchronize if needed.

        Parameters:
        pn - Player number to check
        Returns:
        True if waiting for a reply from pn
        Since:
